        "content": "<p>bongjunj <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12757#issuecomment-4037683109\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/12757\">issue #12757</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/511638f539f1914c5194fc6db286c099f3450ec3/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/lower.isle#L4557\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/511638f539f1914c5194fc6db286c099f3450ec3/cranelift/codegen/src/isa/x64/lower.isle#L4557</a></p>\n<p><code>-1</code> in place of <code>u128</code> seems like an allowed behavior.</p>\n<p>However, <code>-1</code> in place of <code>u64</code> is causing compilation failure (due to invalid Rust code generated).</p>\n</blockquote>",
